ETHICAL ROYALTY SCALE (ERS)

Commercial users must self-assess their activity and remit a percentage of the gross revenue generated by or through the integration of the Software according to the following tiers:

TIER α (8%) – BENEFICIAL: Projects that directly contribute to scientific research, optimization of simulations or computations with societal impact, open education, or environmental solutions.
TIER β (15%) – NEUTRAL: Generic SaaS, business process automation, standard HPC projects, or commercial research without direct societal impact.
TIER Ω (30%) – CHAOS & DESTRUCTION: Exploitation for algorithmic financial speculation, mass surveillance, social manipulation, military, or other harmful applications.

GENESIS CLAUSE: For projects of extreme public utility or global impact without profit motive, the Author may grant a written waiver reducing royalties below 8%.

APEX CEILING: Royalties will never exceed 30%, the maximum cap accepted by the Software.

